I walked in, placed my order, I repeated myself 3 more times. The Deli got crowded some people didn't have a mask on. I told them I was going to be outside and for them to let me know when my order was ready. I had a hard time leaving because it was that crowded. I finally managed to step outside. I waited 10 min but every time I tried going I'm, more people walked in. Finally I managed to go in and told them why don't they enforce the mask policy. Long story short, our breakfast was cold, we threw it out and vowed never to go there again. I live in the area 41 years and was dissatisfied with the food, their I don't care attitude. If you go there be sure to repeat your order and make sure all customers are wearing a mask.

LOHO'S BABY! Loho's got it on lock 24/7 with whatever you need. Y'all remember the room of requirement from Harry Potter?!? LOHO'S IS THAT OF THE LOWER EAST SIDE. Allow me to regale you a story to drown out all this negative nonsense in the reviews below: It was 5am, Saturday morning, the squad trudging drunkenly through the bitter Manhattan tundra. Like any wasted warriors making their way through the urban hellscape that is NYC past midnight, we needed an oasis in the desert. Homie 1 wants pizza, homie 2 wants an omelette, and homie 3 wants a chopped cheese packed to the brim with the works. LOHO'S NOT ONLY prepared ALL THREE orders in approx 7 minutes, but made it WITH CHARISMA AND CLASS. 10/10 WOULD RECOMMEND BRÖTHER. WINGUAAAARDIUM LOHOSA
